= TTF_RenderText_Shaded =

Create an 8-bit palettized surface and render the given text at high quality with the given font and colors.

== Syntax ==

<syntaxhighlight lang='c'>
SDL_Surface * TTF_RenderText_Shaded(TTF_Font *font,
                const char *text, SDL_Color fg, SDL_Color bg);
</syntaxhighlight>

== Function Parameters ==

{|
|'''font'''
|[[TTF_Font]] handle
|-
|'''text'''
|text to render
|-
|'''fg'''
|foreground color
|-
|'''bg'''
|background color
|}

== Return Value ==

Returns the new surface, or NULL if there was an error.

== Remarks ==

The 0 pixel is background, while other pixels have varying degrees of the
foreground color. This function returns the new surface, or NULL if there
was an error.

